  "prompt": "Why are newspapers like The Economic Times, Financial Times and others printed on pink paper?",
  "response": "Newspapers like The Economic Times and Financial Times are printed on pink paper primarily for branding reasons. This distinct color helps them stand out from other newspapers, making them instantly recognizable to readers and advertisers. The tradition of using pink paper dates back to the early 19th century when The Financial Times adopted it as a way to differentiate itself from competitors. Besides distinctive branding, some claim that pinkish paper reduces glare and is easier on the eyes, enhancing readability, though this is not the primary reason for the choice of color.",
